summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 7917, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Pike Street, in the City of Seattle, between First Avenue and a point two hundred (200) feet west of the west margin of First Avenue, by curbing and planking the same, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Immediate Payment," under the provisions of Ordinance No. 5693 of said city, approved December 6, 1899."
